The firm began in the 1930's with the production of sprout and hop picking machines. A small part of the business is still devoted to the production of spare parts, which are exported as far as Africa and Australia. A land drainage machine was then developed for both home and export markets, but this has seriously declined with the removal of the government's land drainage subsidy.
At present the company is involved in the design and production of a revolutionary recovery vehicle for British Rail. It is basically a four wheel drive lorry chassis, which is capable of travelling on roads, rough terrain and railway tracks.
